-1765748359.text: "Ivacaftor activated CFTR dependent chloride transport in non CF epithelia and ameliorated the functional CFTR defect induced by smoke to 185 +/-36% of non CF control (P < 0.05), thereby increasing airway surface liquid (from 7.3 +/-0.6 microm to 10.1 +/-0.4 microm, P < 0.005) and mucociliary transport (from 0.27 +/-0.11 microm/s to 2.7 +/-0.28 microm/s, P < 0.005)."
